But any time I am in the company of my friends and am having a wonderful time laughing, talking joyously, etc. I am reminded one must also struggle. There are many who have struggled for it to be possible for me to have fun with my friends... And we must also struggle for others.

Friendship truly is magic. I love my friends, as ones in real life, so also here. Spending time with people you love is wonderful and joyous. Epicurus and his ideal of a garden full of friends having a wonderful time together talking, having a simple joy, etc. is truly visionary.

One thing in the Hagakure that struck me was a saying that even if you are on your deathbed literally dying, if you have unfinished business you can still use your willpower and struggle against death to live for a day or two more before succumbing to death. Mitani Jokyu's saying

You can be dying of a terrible disease ill in delirium but as long as you are still alive you have your willpower and are able to struggle so you can prolong your death for a little bit. Maybe wait a few hours so a loved one can arrive from far away to visit you. You are able to.

Something Fr. Stephen de Young mentioned on Lord of Spirits podcast is that we tend to think of the different ranks of angels as different "species" of angels, but the truth is closer to that each single individual angel is a separate species in himself. It's not like in biology.
